      "value": "<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #191813; -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; vertical-align: baseline; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">At 10th level, you can use your action to restore some of your party's shields. Choose up to 5 friendly creatures with shields you can see. Hack into their armor system and use a brute force algorithm to overload their kinetic barrier. Roll 4d8. Each creature immediately gains that many shield points, even if their total shield point capacity is less than the amount rolled.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #191813; -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; vertical-align: baseline; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">Once you use this feature, you must finish a short or long rest before you can use it again.</p>",
